g.title: Various tools for creating and manipulating Zarr V3 data with the zarrs rust crate - A reencoder that can change codecs, chunk shape, convert Zarr V2 to V3, etc. - Create an OME-Zarr hierarchy from a Zarr array. - Transform arrays: crop, rescale, downsample, gradient magnitude, gaussian, noise filtering, etc.
A library for OME-Zarr (previously OME-NGFF) metadata.

`icechunk` store support. - git-like version control for Zarr hierachies. - Read "virtual Zarr datacubes" of archival formats (e.g., netCDF4, HDF5, etc.) created by `VirtualiZarr` and backed by `icechunk`.
A storage adapter for zip files.
The Zarr extension point registry for `zarrs` (re-exported as `zarrs::registry`).
The core library for manipulating Zarr hierarchies.
A subset of `zarrs` exposed as a C/C++ API.
The data type extension API for `zarrs` (re-exported in `zarrs::array::data_type`).
